keep them with care, and even when adult do not for&s;ake them&mdash;the whole
brood thus live in a family toge|ther&mdash;each family afterwards live apart,
and hunt in concert&mdash;upon the returning &s;ea&s;on of court&s;hip, this
union is at an end, the family parts for ever, each to e&s;tabli&s;h a little
hou&s;hold of his own, v. 135&mdash;the manner of flying is always up and down,
&s;eldom direct or &s;ideways&mdash;different kinds of this bird, v. 136</ITEM>
