<HI>kough-footed eagle,</HI> of the <HI>white-tailed eagle,</HI> of the
<HI>erne,</HI> of the <HI>black eagle,</HI> v. 97&mdash;of the
<HI>&s;ea-eagle,</HI> of the <HI>o&s;prey,</HI> of the <HI>jean le blanc,</HI>
of the <HI>Bra&s;il eagle,</HI> of the <HI>Oroonoko eagle,</HI> of the
<HI>crowned African eagle,</HI> of the <HI>eagle</HI> of <HI>Pondicherry,</HI>
v. 98, 99</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Ears,</HI> di&s;tingui&s;hing features in
quadrupeds&mdash;&s;erve in them as principal marks of the
pa&s;&s;ions&mdash;&s;malle&s;t <PB REF="298"> ears in men &s;aid to be mo&s;t
beautiful&mdash;the large&s;t the be&s;t for hearing&mdash;&s;ome &s;avage
