Molucca i&s;lands&mdash;in Africa&mdash;in America, tho&s;e of the
Andes&mdash;tho&s;e of Arequipa, Cara&s;&s;a, Malahallo and Cotopaxi, i.
99&mdash;de&s;cription of the latter by Ulloa; and an erup|tion of it, i.
100</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Mou&s;e,</HI> the mo&s;t feeble, and mo&s;t timid of all
quadru|peds, except the Guinea-pig, iv. 72&mdash;never ren|dered quite
familiar; though fed in a cage, retains its apprehen&s;ions&mdash;no animal has
more enemies, and few &s;o incapable of re&s;i&s;tance&mdash;the owl, cat,
&s;nake, hawk, wea&s;el, and rat de&s;troy them by millions&mdash;brings forth
