the variety of mou&s;e-traps&mdash;long-tailed field-mou&s;e, iv.
74&mdash;&s;hort-tailed field-mou&s;e&mdash;has a &s;tore again&s;t winter, a
bu&s;hel at a time&mdash;a de&s;cription of the &s;hrew-mou&s;e, iv. 75</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Mou&s;toc,</HI> or <HI>white-no&s;e,</HI> monkey of the
ancient con|tinent; <PB REF="407"> a beautiful little animal&mdash;its
de&s;cription iv. 234</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Mouth</HI> of hares lined with hair&mdash;the only
animals that have it on the in&s;ide, iv. 8&mdash;the &s;nails of the tro|chus
