iii. 233&mdash;our fir&s;t were brought from the Ea&s;t Indies; and they are
&s;till found in flocks in a wild &s;tate in the i&s;lands of Java and
Ceylon&mdash;the common people of Italy &s;ay it has the plumage of an angel,
the voice of a devil, and the guts of a thief&mdash;in the days of Solomon we
find his navies imported from the Ea&s;t apes and peacocks, v. 171&mdash;Aelian
